# Agent config map — the "director".
#
# One shared source of truth (this repo = the hub). Each agent tool reads its instructions from
# a hardcoded location; install.sh reads this map and symlinks that location back to a hub file.
# You edit the hub; install.sh projects it into every tool. Add a tool = add a line here.
#
# Columns (whitespace-separated):
#   tool   load-point (where the tool reads its global rules)   hub-file   mode
#
# mode (how install.sh wires the load-point; defaults to link if the column is absent):
#   link   symlink the load-point straight at the hub file. Live-sync (edit core.md → every
#          link-mode tool sees it instantly), but the tool gets ONLY the shared rules — there
#          is nowhere to add private overlay rules.
#   block  write a REAL file at the load-point with a managed fenced block holding the hub
#          file's contents; your private rules live OUTSIDE the fence in the same file and
#          survive every re-run. Use this for tools that can't @import a second file (Codex).
#          Trade-off: not live — re-run setup/install.sh to resync the block after editing
#          core.md. setup/doctor.sh FAILs if a block has drifted.
#
# Claude is handled specially by install.sh (personal layer: its file @imports core.md and
# CLAUDE.md symlinks to it), so it is intentionally NOT listed here.

codex      ~/.codex/AGENTS.md                   core.md   block
gemini     ~/.gemini/GEMINI.md                  core.md   link
opencode   ~/.config/opencode/AGENTS.md         core.md   link
